@Polar: reloadUsers is called upon a new request (zite update). The endRequest function is also called upon zite update which removes the loading stuff. The reloadUsers function looks through the "users" section of the "users" and "users_archived" json files. Then it searches for the current users auth address by calling the searchAuthAddress function:

```
reloadUsers: ->
		@setStatusTitle("Loading users data (1/2)...")
		@cmd "fileGet", "data/users_archive.json", (res) =>
			@users = JSON.parse(res)["users"]
			@setStatusTitle("Loading users data (2/2)...")
			@cmd "fileGet", "data/users.json", (res) =>
				for user, data of JSON.parse(res)["users"]
					@users[user] = data
				gotauth = false
				@searchAuthAddress @auth_address, (user_name, cert) =>
					@setStatusTitle("")
					if cert
						[auth_type, auth_address, cert_sign] = cert.split(",")
						@setCert(auth_type, user_name, cert_sign)
						gotauth = true
					else
						$(".panel-intro").addClass("noauth")
```

